In this article, President Barack Obama proclaims the week ending on Thanksgiving Day of each year as National Farm-City Week. He highlights the contributions of farmers and ranchers in supplying the basic necessities of daily life, managing fertile land, and caring for natural resources. The president emphasizes the importance of cultivating relationships between farmers, rural businesses, and urban/suburban communities. He acknowledges the role of agriculture in enhancing national security and prosperity and calls for the sustainability of farming for future generations. The article also mentions the celebration of farms and the recognition of the ties between urban/suburban communities and local farmers through regional food systems, farmers markets, and community gardens. President Obama urges Americans to reflect on the accomplishments of those dedicated to promoting agricultural abundance and environmental stewardship during the Thanksgiving season.